node.text:
9 months pregnant and 9 months postpartum.

Third baby, two miscarriages. So incredible that our bodies can grow these tiny humans. I never felt sexier in my life than when I was pregnant, even at my fullest. I’m one of those women who even with all the symptoms in the world, I truly enjoyed every bit of being pregnant. Was it all butterflies and rainbows? No, but I’d do it all over again because there is no greater feeling than feeling those kicks and moves. So to all the girls that are afraid to get pregnant, don’t be, it’s a beautiful journey. To all the moms that are currently pregnant, you can do this! The ride is short lived. Our bodies are amazing!

.
Reposted from @karlamarquez_
#9monthsin9monthsout ##9monthspregnant #9monthspostpartum #postpartumbody #postpartum #momof3 #babynumber3 #preggo #pregnancy

node.text:
“The boobs are big the belly is big the body is big. Man.. pregnancy is hard. 
Giving it up to all mamas who make it look effortless... this journey is hard as hell and also incredibly special. Lovely to have a little life inside and to day dream of all the new adventures to come, buuuut almost impossible to get my own shoes on. Sick of getting up 9 times a night to pee and looking at this weird body in the mirror that is not my own at the moment. Women are so bad ass, this was just a note to remind myself and remind others how strong and beautiful you are! 
WE GOT THIS.” .

.
📸: @hilaryduff

node.text:
“A couple of weeks ago I was 5 weeks pregnant. Now I’m not. One morning at work that changed my course of motherhood. I’ve paced in my mind about whether or not to share this, but the stigma and awkwardness I’ve felt about it is the reason I’m sharing. I’ve had so many people from work reach out to check on me. I feel so loved and supported. I’m urging all moms that are dealing with depression, miscarriage, or any pregnancy/motherhood difficulties to reach out for help. The sadness I felt was unlike any other. My husband was my rock and driving force. You are not alone, mama. Praying for comfort to all moms everywhere. Today and always. XO”
.

.
| #pregnancylife #momtobe
| 📸 @simpleheartco
.

node.text:
Sometimes the strongest among us are the ones who smile through silent pain, cry behind closed doors, and fight battles nobody knows about.
⠀
To all of our mamas who have fought and are currently fighting infertility, or healing from miscarriages or infant loss, our hearts go out to you. We hope you know that you aren’t alone, and the pain will someday go away. The greater the storm, the brighter the rainbow

.
📸: @as_im_waiting

.

node.text:
𝘛𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘴𝘶𝘤𝘩 𝘢 𝘣𝘦𝘢𝘶𝘵𝘪𝘧𝘶𝘭 𝘴𝘵𝘰𝘳𝘺. 𝘓𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳𝘴𝘦𝘭𝘧, 𝘭𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘣𝘰𝘥𝘺. 𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘢𝘮𝘢𝘻𝘪𝘯𝘨𝘭𝘺 𝘣𝘦𝘢𝘶𝘵𝘪𝘧𝘶𝘭 💕⁣
⁣
There are days I get disgusted with my own body or feel uncomfortable with myself, but those same days I remind myself of how wonderful and strong a women’s body is. I was capable of creating a human. I was able to give life. This was your home for 38 weeks and 6 days. Where you felt safe, ate, and moved around. ⁣
⁣
My water broke Dec 26, 2018 at 8:30 am and was in labor for 14 hrs and pushed for 45 min I gave birth to a beautiful girl on Dec 27, 2018 at 12:29 am⁣
⁣
Recovery was painful, breastfeeding was painful. This is me. Where I am constantly leaking. Every time I look at my body all I see are, stretch marks on my belly, thighs, and butt. Some girls get lucky and don’t end up with one stretch mark. But I wasn’t, I am not one of those. My body won’t be the same, I’ll have these marks. And I’m learning to love them because it’s just a reminder of my first pregnancy, a new journey, a new life. 💛💛💛⁣

Say something positive about yourself below 💕
⁣
Repost: @luptits
